			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: The Taken King &amp; Patch 2.0
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1840841">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							I posted a bit in the September releases, but here's kind of my rundown for Destiny since release<br />
<br />
Major Release problems: Shitty story, no dedicated servers+shitty netcode (if you were lagging you were almost invulnerable <b><u>in PvE</u></b> as well as PvP), extremely grindy.<br />
<br />
The first DLC did nothing to address those problems.  They patched in some minor fixes for the grindyness overtime, but it was the second DLC that in my opinion did a lot to solve the problems:  The story for the House of Wolves was pretty well done, you had a lot of interaction with NPC's, it added a better Quest structure than what the game originally had, and it bumped the rewards for everything from garbage being a surprise reward, to Legendary items being an uncommon reward, and pretty constantly getting Rare rewards.<br />
<br />
TTK has completely solved the Extremely Grindy part in my opinion.  The only thing you should really have to grind at this point is XP to level your new subclass, and that is the type of thing that happens while you play normally.<br />
<br />
The first quest for TTK has more story and expositional dialogue than pretty much the entire base game.[1]<br />
<br />
If you decide to give TTK a chance, the expansion comes with a token you can redeem for a free level 25 character, which lets you skip the original story and create a new character you want.<br />
<br />
My current level 40 (cap) character is a Warlock. I've only played with the 'Sith Lord' spec, but the 'Sun God Thor' spec for Titans looks pretty amazing too.  I think the Hunter spec looks like trash (Wee, Crowd Control! How Exciting!), but I'll probably level it up this coming weekend, since it only takes a few hours max to level from 34 to 40 and get the subclass.  Getting it was pretty fucking awesome, I imagine the other 2 classes will also have some awesome events.<br />
<br />
<a href="http://xboxclips.com/GentlemanJack/341b3306-7647-4a33-8628-b049c9f2a1bc/embed" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://xboxclips.com/GentlemanJack/3...c9f2a1bc/embed</a><br />
<br />
<br />
[1] I should mention that the base game now also has a lot more expositional dialogue they added in with the ghost and Quest Text, but I didn't play through the entire game again to have an accurate estimate.  I would say if you ranked 1-10 where 1 is the story detail of Peggle, and a 10 is Last of Us, the original game was like a 4, and the expansion is at running around an 8.  I was level 34 doing a level 25 quest, and I was still tense during the intro mission
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
