				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: The Taken King &amp; Patch 2.0
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1841256">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Wool</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=7fc66ab734cac309c8890df4e482c46e&amp;p=1841191#post1841191" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">How is the new content itself? Has the level design evolved any? I don't really expect it to, but I'm curious. The original game's (and the DLC) single player content was fine, but not very exciting. The House of Wolves was a little better, but not enough to write home about (though I did like the new characters).<br />
<br />
Anyone with not enough time to explain why they don't have enough time to explain?</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>I'm not sure what you mean by level design.  The entire way story is delivered has changed.  Grimoire only delivers back story now, or how your story has progressed from other view-points, and the current information is conveyed by questing (exactly like WoW) and NPC's talking to you in a group chat during missions (similar to WoW, except instead of quest text, it's a voice over).<br />
<br />
I had to search around a bit to find a version of the first mission that wasn't full of garbage from leaked playthroughs (which purposely left out dialog) or had super obnoxious players babbling about shit constantly, this is the best I could come up with: <a href="https://youtu.be/Yh1ra0cGi4U?t=302" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">https://youtu.be/Yh1ra0cGi4U?t=302</a><br />
<br />
Although I feel like watching that makes the mission drastically less tense.  Like the first time I did the mission I moved strategically through the level, took cover, etc.  The second time I did it I sprinted through and Gjallerhorned everything I didn't just vault past (it's a level 25 mission, and I was level 34).  That's part of what makes this difficult to explain.  How do you convey how much better something as subjective as story is without just showing someone the story?  It's drastically better<br />
<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>FilanFyretracker</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=7fc66ab734cac309c8890df4e482c46e&amp;p=1841197#post1841197" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">I am curious has the tower expanded any?  I have kept hoping one day we could wander down into the city XD</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>No, the people in the city are terrified of Guardians, because you're zombies and have terrifying space magic.  I've also heard a lot of them referred to as feral humans, but I don't know exactly what that means.  <br />
<br />
But more seriously, there is a Crucible Map on top of a tall building in the city, but that's as close as you get.  In general, this is one of the things I've been disappointed about with the game.  Earth contains only Russia, when there are a few different areas I think would be cool for a one-off mission or cut scene.  I think all things considered, I'd rather explore the Reef.  The remaining people on Earth were those who were abandoned by the planet-wide evacuation, and the Awoken are those who managed to get a decent distance before being nearly completely obliterated.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
